Use the standard library
This is how to count_upper of s:
   Remember that count is 0
   Remember that seen is 0
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this s's length times:
      Remember that c is item i in s
      When c is at least 65, then:
         When c is at most 90, then:
            Increase seen
            When seen is 2, then:
               Increase count
            End when
         End when
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is count
Now you know
>>> count_upper of [97, 66, 67, 100, 69, 102]
1
>>> count_upper of [97, 98, 99, 100, 101, 102, 103]
0
>>> count_upper of [100, 66, 66, 69]
0